Maintainer: Nima Hejazi <nh@nimahejazi.org>
Description: Targeted maximum likelihood (TML) estimation of population-level
    causal effects in mediation analysis. The causal effects are defined by
    joint static or stochastic interventions applied to the exposure and the
    mediator. Targeted doubly robust estimators are provided for the classical
    natural direct and indirect effects, as well as the more recently developed
    population intervention direct and indirect effects.
